figure 4a

qqplots

We got the T1D GWAS SNPs p values from QTL mapping on immune phenotypes using R package MatrixeQTL. We showed in qqplot how T1D GWAS loci influence immune phenotypes in 300DM.

library(ggplot2)
library(RColorBrewer)

Immune cell proportion

dat<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/qq_plot/cc/forest_cc_p.txt",header=T)

anno<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/qq_plot/cc/anno.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t")

###
dat1<-dat[which(as.character(dat$cytokine)%in%rownames(anno)),]

tmp<-as.character(dat1$cytokine)

subpopulation=rep(NA,length(tmp))

for (i in 1:length(tmp)){
  cyto<-tmp[i]
  subpopulation[i]<-as.character(anno[cyto,3])
}

dat1<-transform(dat1,Subpopulation=subpopulation)

dat1$Subpopulation<-as.factor(dat1$Subpopulation)
or<-rev(order(dat1$SNP))
dat1<-dat1[or,]

dat1$SNP<-factor(dat1$SNP,levels=unique(dat1$SNP))

dat1<-transform(dat1,logp=(-log10(p)))

p_group<-split(dat1,dat1$Subpopulation)

EXPPVAL<-function(my.pvalues){(rank(my.pvalues, ties.method="first")+.5)/(length(my.pvalues)+1)}

y<-lapply(p_group,function(w){p<-w$p;EXPPVAL(p)})

p<-c(y$`B cells`,y$Lymphocytes,y$Monocytes,y$`NK cells`,y$`T cell Prol`,y$`T cells`,y$`T Reg`,y$WBC)
Subpopulation<-c(rep('B cells',length(y$`B cells`)),rep('Lymphocytes',length(y$Lymphocytes)),rep("Monocytes",length(y$Monocytes)),rep("NK cells",length(y$`NK cells`)),rep("T cell Prol",length(y$`T cell Prol`)),rep("T cells",length(y$`T cells`)),rep("T Reg",length(y$`T Reg`)),rep("WBC",length(y$WBC)))
exp<-data.frame(p,Subpopulation)
exp<-transform(exp,logp=(-log10(p)))

or<-order(dat1$Subpopulation)
dat1<-dat1[or,]

tmp<-data.frame('obs'=dat1$logp,'exp'=exp$logp,Subpopulation=dat1$Subpopulation)

tmp<-subset(tmp,Subpopulation!="WBC")
tmp<-subset(tmp,Subpopulation!="Lymphocytes")

tmp$Subpopulation<-factor(tmp$Subpopulation,levels=c("B cells","T cells","Monocytes","NK cells","T cell Prol","T Reg"))

ggplot(data=tmp,aes(x=exp,y=obs,color=Subpopulation))+geom_point()+geom_abline(slope = 1,intercept = 0,lty=2,color="grey20")+theme_bw()+scale_color_brewer(palette="Set1")

cytokine production

dat<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/qq_plot/cytokine/forest_cyto_p.txt",header=T)

anno<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/qq_plot/cytokine/anno.txt",header=T,row.names = 1)

tmp<-as.character(dat$cytokine)
type=rep(NA,length(tmp))
for (i in 1:length(tmp)){
  cyto<-tmp[i]
  type[i]<-as.character(anno[cyto,4])
}

tmp<-as.character(dat$cytokine)
cytokine_type=rep(NA,length(tmp))
for (i in 1:length(tmp)){
  cyto<-tmp[i]
  cytokine_type[i]<-as.character(anno[cyto,5])
}

dat<-transform(dat,type=type,cytokine_type=cytokine_type)
dat$type<-as.factor(dat$type)
dat$cytokine_type<-as.factor(dat$cytokine_type)

or<-rev(order(dat$SNP))
dat<-dat[or,]

dat$SNP<-factor(dat$SNP,levels = unique(dat$SNP))
dat<-transform(dat,logp=(-log10(p)))
p_group<-split(dat,dat$type)

EXPPVAL<-function(my.pvalues){(rank(my.pvalues, ties.method="first")+.5)/(length(my.pvalues)+1)}

y<-lapply(p_group,function(w){p<-w$p;EXPPVAL(p)})

p<-c(y$`24h`,y$`7d`)
Subpopulation<-c(rep('24h',length(y$`24h`)),rep('7d',length(y$'7d')))
exp<-data.frame(p,Subpopulation)
exp<-transform(exp,logp=(-log10(p)))

or<-order(dat$type)
dat<-dat[or,]

tmp<-data.frame('obs'=dat$logp,'exp'=exp$logp,type=dat$type)
ggplot(data=tmp,aes(x=exp,y=obs,color=type))+geom_point()+geom_abline(slope = 1,intercept = 0,lty=2,color="grey20")+theme_bw()

p_group<-split(dat,dat$cytokine_type)

p<-c(y$`TNF-a`,y$`MCP-1`,y$`IL-8`,y$`IL-6`,y$`IL-1RA`,y$`IL-1b`,y$`IL-10`,y$`IL-22`,y$`IL-17`,y$IFNy)
Subpopulation<-c(rep('TNF-a',length(y$`TNF-a`)),rep('MCP-1',length(y$'MCP-1')),rep('IL-8',length(y$'IL-8')),rep('IL-6',length(y$'IL-6')),rep('IL-1RA',length(y$'IL-1RA')),rep('IL-1b',length(y$'IL-1b')),rep('IL-10',length(y$'IL-10')),rep('IL-22',length(y$'IL-22')),rep('IL-17',length(y$'IL-17')),rep('IFNy',length(y$'IFNy')))
exp<-data.frame(p,Subpopulation)
exp<-transform(exp,logp=(-log10(p)))

dat$cytokine_type<-factor(dat$cytokine_type,levels = c("TNF-a","MCP-1","IL-8","IL-6","IL-1RA","IL-1b","IL-10","IL-22","IL-17","IFNy"))
or<-order(dat$cytokine_type)
dat<-dat[or,]
